Package atm.view

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    View
    This is the standard interface View for the MVC setup.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccountSelectView
    The AccountSelectView allows the user to select an account they would like to interact with.
    AmountView
    The AmountView view is where the user is allowed to enter the amoun they would like to transfer or withdraw.
    BackgroundPanel
    Support custom painting on a panel in the form of a) images - that can be scaled, tiled or painted at original size b) non solid painting - that can be done by using a Paint object Also, any component added directly to this panel will be made non-opaque so that the custom painting can show through.
    BalanceView
    The BalanceView is the view the user sees when they are viewing the balances of their accounts.
    FixLabelSize  
    JFrameView
    This is the standard abstract JFrameView class for the MVC setup.
    JNumericField
    NEED DESCRIPTION OF WHAT THIS DOES
    LoginView
    The LoginView is what the user sees when logging into the ATM.
    LogoutView
    The LogoutView is the view the user sees when logging out of the system.
    MainView
    The MainView the user sees when using the application.
    Misc
    The Misc class contains all the misc.
    PINScreen
    The PIN Screen allows the user to enter their 4-digit PIN that is associated to their card.
    RequestFocusListener
    Convenience class to request focus on a component.
    SelectionView
    These are the types of selections the ATM allows.
    WithdrawView
    The WithdrawView is the view the user will see when they select the withdraw option on the ATM.
